text: Every day is relearning how to live I m not sure how much longer I can do it  Wake up  Get out of bed  Shower  Work  just remind myself of the routine while I hope things improve  People say things get better but I m having trouble believing it  Depressed for as long as I can remember and finally diagnosed and medicated   years ago  I try to keep up on hobbies and have something to look forward to but that gets harder every day The last   years have been a complete waste and it feels impossible to come back from that  There s the ex gf that broke up with me on he day that I was going to propose  Had the ring in my pocket  even  Thought it was perfect but found out later she d been cheating  Went from her to a girl I married in spite of red flags  I thought I couldn t do any better and just dealt with her emotional abuse  I m now divorced and being forced to sell my house and move in with parents in my late  s  Just a complete failure  I m looking at being stuck living with them for years while I pay down the debt I m in thanks to ex wife   Then there are the friends  I already don t have many and try to fake happy but they still fade away or cut contact  Even that gf mentioned above  I tried to hate her but couldn t and we were friendly a couple years later but recently  she called  I thought just to catch up but no  she was just beating around the bush before saying goodbye for good   Nothing gets better  The few things that are good that I hold hope for just crumble  I should have listened when my ex wife told me to kill myself

text: My own worst enemy was always myselfI ve been told how scary I am when I get angry  and how broken I look when I m sad  The anger and sadness have both dropped away now  and all that s left is a numbness and a sense of singular purpose to escape No one took my first attempt seriously at the age of twelve despite my reason being   I wanted to die I put a gun in my mouth but couldn t pull the trigger at age eighteen   I knew something was horribly wrong before I got my autoimmune diagnosis for  three years  before I did anything despite leaking blood on a daily basis  and even that was at someone else s insistence I stopped taking the highway to work because the idea of yanking the wheel over and smashing the car was a daily draw   Had a complete breakdown at one job  which led to my firing seven months to the day from my return Nearly walked out on the subway tracks to put a foot onto the third rail  More than once I m past middle age  lost my job  I ve been fighting with insurance companies for a month to try to get the medication that keeps me alive I gave up Wednesday  I m done I ve fought long and hard  and I simply don t have it in me any more
